---
/**
 * bloom-0001 · Figure 2 — "the asymmetry is the whole point".
 *
 * Copied VERBATIM from docs/bloom-filters/lessons/0001-what-is-a-bloom-filter.html
 * (figure + svg + figcaption incl. the footnote <sup id="r1b">). Lives as an
 * .astro component for the same reason as Fig1: raw inline SVG with kebab-case
 * attributes is unreliable inside MDX, but is plain HTML inside .astro.
 */
---

<figure>
    <svg
        xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg"
        viewBox="0 0 600 230"
        font-family="ui-sans-serif,system-ui,sans-serif"
    >
        <defs>
            <marker
                id="ad"
                viewBox="0 0 10 10"
                refX="8"
                refY="5"
                markerWidth="7"
                markerHeight="7"
                orient="auto-start-reverse"
            >
                <path d="M0 0L10 5L0 10z" fill="#136f63"></path>
            </marker>
        </defs>
        <rect x="0" y="0" width="600" height="230" fill="#fffff8"></rect>
        <text x="300" y="26" text-anchor="middle" font-size="15" fill="#0f4f47" font-weight="bold"
            >One decision: is ANY checked bit 0?</text
        >
        <rect x="210" y="46" width="180" height="44" rx="8" fill="#e8f1ef" stroke="#136f63"></rect>
        <text x="300" y="68" text-anchor="middle" font-size="14" fill="#0f4f47"
            >query(x): check k bits</text
        >
        <text x="300" y="84" text-anchor="middle" font-size="11" fill="#6b675f">any bit = 0?</text>
        <path
            d="M260 90 L150 130"
            fill="none"
            stroke="#136f63"
            stroke-width="1.5"
            marker-end="url(#ad)"></path>
        <path
            d="M340 90 L450 130"
            fill="none"
            stroke="#136f63"
            stroke-width="1.5"
            marker-end="url(#ad)"></path>
        <text x="180" y="116" text-anchor="middle" font-size="12" fill="#2f5d3a" font-weight="bold"
            >YES, a 0</text
        >
        <text x="420" y="116" text-anchor="middle" font-size="12" fill="#7a5e12" font-weight="bold"
            >NO, all 1</text
        >
        <rect x="30" y="132" width="240" height="62" rx="8" fill="#eef5ee" stroke="#2f5d3a"></rect>
        <text x="150" y="158" text-anchor="middle" font-size="15" fill="#2f5d3a" font-weight="bold"
            >DEFINITELY ABSENT</text
        >
        <text x="150" y="178" text-anchor="middle" font-size="11" fill="#2f5d3a"
            >certain &#8212; no false negatives</text
        >
        <rect x="330" y="132" width="240" height="62" rx="8" fill="#fbf3e6" stroke="#9a7a17"></rect>
        <text x="450" y="158" text-anchor="middle" font-size="15" fill="#7a5e12" font-weight="bold"
            >PROBABLY PRESENT</text
        >
        <text x="450" y="178" text-anchor="middle" font-size="11" fill="#7a5e12"
            >maybe a false positive &#8212; verify</text
        >
        <text x="300" y="216" text-anchor="middle" font-size="12" fill="#6b675f"
            >One missing bit is proof; all bits set can be coincidence.</text
        >
    </svg>
    <figcaption>
        If <em>any</em> of x's k bits is 0, x was never added. All k bits set can coincide from <em
            >other</em
        > items, so "present" is only a probability.<sup><a href="#s1" id="r1b">1</a></sup>
    </figcaption>
</figure>
